Question 1:

Why String is immutable in java and what is the difference between String and String Builder? And Write some
of the methods of String class at least 5 with example.
Answer:
*The strings are immutable in java because of security concurrency,class loading 
*The string is immutable in java and the string builder is mutable in java.
The method in string class are the inbuilt method which are used on strings
Examples:
concat():concat string to the end of other string
endsWith():check the end with specialcharector
equals():compare two strings and return true or false
format(): check the format and the argument in specified cocation;
indexOf():Return the index of the string